.TH MCP\-SERVER\-WEBDRIVER 1 "2026-06-25" "0.5.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mcp\-server\-webdriver \- MCP server for AI\-assisted browser automation via Selenium WebDriver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mcp\-server\-webdriver
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mcp\-server\-webdriver
is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that exposes Firefox browser
automation as tools for AI assistants such as Claude.
It eliminates the need to manually copy\-paste browser DevTools output by
giving the assistant direct access to:
.IP \(bu 4
JavaScript exceptions (type, message, file, line, column, stack trace)
.IP \(bu 4
Console output (\fBconsole.log\fR / \fBwarn\fR / \fBerror\fR / \fBinfo\fR / \fBdebug\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
Failed network resources \(em broken CSS, JS, images, fonts (4xx\|/\|5xx\|/\|DNS)
.IP \(bu 4
Slow resources (configurable threshold, default 2000\~ms)
.IP \(bu 4
Full\-page screenshots for layout and CSS regression diagnosis
.IP \(bu 4
Computed CSS on any element
.IP \(bu 4
DOM structure of any element (outerHTML)
.PP
Communication is over \fBstdin\fR/\fBstdout\fR using the MCP protocol (JSON\-RPC 2.0
with Content\-Length framing).
The server is launched automatically by the MCP client; it is not normally
invoked by hand.
.PP
DevTools capture requires the W3C WebDriver BiDi protocol, supported by
Firefox with geckodriver \(>= 0.34.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-P \fIprofile\fR
Start Firefox with the named profile \fIprofile\fR.
Equivalent to setting \fBFIREFOX_PROFILE\fR=\fIprofile\fR in the environment.
.TP
.B \-\-profile \fIpath\fR
Start Firefox using the profile directory at \fIpath\fR.
Equivalent to setting \fBFIREFOX_PROFILE_DIR\fR=\fIpath\fR in the environment.
If both \fB\-\-profile\fR and \fB\-P\fR are given, \fB\-\-profile\fR takes precedence.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a summary of usage and available tools, then exit.
.SH TOOLS
The server exposes 37 MCP tools grouped by category.
.SS Session management
.TP
.B browser_open
Open Firefox.
The \fIurl\fR parameter is optional (default: \fBabout:blank\fR).
Bare hostnames (e.g. \fIexample.com\fR) are accepted; \fBhttps://\fR is prepended
automatically.
Accepts \fIheadless\fR (default true), \fIenable_bidi\fR (default true),
\fIgeckodriver_log\fR, and \fIfirefox_binary\fR parameters.
.TP
.B browser_close
Close the browser session and discard all buffered DevTools data.
.TP
.B browser_status
Return session state, geckodriver source/version, BiDi status, and
buffer counts as JSON.
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B browser_navigate
Navigate to a URL.
Bare hostnames get \fBhttps://\fR prepended automatically.
.TP
.B browser_back
Navigate back in history.
.TP
.B browser_forward
Navigate forward in history.
.TP
.B browser_refresh
Reload the current page.
.SS Page inspection
.TP
.B browser_screenshot
Capture a PNG screenshot of the full page, or of a specific element
when a CSS selector is given.
.TP
.B browser_get_title
Return the current page \fB<title>\fR.
.TP
.B browser_get_url
Return the current URL.
.TP
.B browser_get_source
Return the full HTML source of the current page.
.TP
.B browser_get_text
Return visible text content, optionally scoped to a CSS selector.
.TP
.B browser_get_attribute
Return the value of an HTML attribute on a matched element.
.TP
.B browser_find_elements
Return a list of all elements matching a CSS selector.
Each entry includes: index, tag, text, id, class, href, src, value,
type, name, aria_label, visible.
Accepts an optional \fIlimit\fR parameter (default 50).
.SS Interaction
.TP
.B browser_click
Click an element identified by a CSS selector.
.TP
.B browser_fill
Type text into an input field.
The field is cleared first by default (\fIclear_first\fR=true).
.TP
.B browser_select
Choose an option in a \fB<select>\fR dropdown by visible text, value, or index.
.TP
.B browser_execute_js
Execute JavaScript and return the result as JSON (falls back to string
for non-serialisable values).
.TP
.B browser_wait
Wait until an element satisfies a condition.
The \fIcondition\fR parameter accepts:
\fBvisible\fR (default), \fBclickable\fR, \fBpresent\fR, or \fBtext:\fR\fIstring\fR.
.TP
.B browser_scroll
Scroll the page or an element.
Pass a CSS selector to scroll that element into view.
Pass \fIx\fR/\fIy\fR to jump to absolute scroll coordinates.
Pass \fIby\fR=true with \fIx\fR/\fIy\fR to scroll relative to the current position.
.TP
.B browser_press_key
Send a keyboard key to an element or the active element.
Supported keys: \fBenter\fR, \fBtab\fR, \fBescape\fR, \fBspace\fR, \fBbackspace\fR,
\fBdelete\fR, \fBhome\fR, \fBend\fR, \fBpageup\fR, \fBpagedown\fR,
\fBarrowup\fR/\fBdown\fR/\fBleft\fR/\fBright\fR (also: \fBup\fR/\fBdown\fR/\fBleft\fR/\fBright\fR),
\fBf1\fR\(en\fBf12\fR.
.TP
.B browser_hover
Move the mouse over an element.
Triggers CSS \fB:hover\fR states and \fBmouseenter\fR/\fBmouseover\fR event listeners —
essential for dropdown menus and tooltips.
.TP
.B browser_switch_frame
Switch the WebDriver context into an \fB<iframe>\fR or back to the main document.
.SS Dialogs and cookies
.TP
.B browser_accept_dialog
Accept (click OK) a JavaScript \fBalert()\fR, \fBconfirm()\fR, or \fBprompt()\fR.
.TP
.B browser_dismiss_dialog
Dismiss (click Cancel) a JavaScript \fBconfirm()\fR or \fBprompt()\fR.
.TP
.B browser_get_cookies
Return all cookies for the current page as a list of dicts.
.TP
.B browser_set_cookie
Set a cookie on the current page.
Useful for injecting auth tokens or session cookies without a login flow.
.SS DevTools (require BiDi)
BiDi listeners are attached automatically when \fBbrowser_open\fR is called
with \fIenable_bidi\fR=true (the default).
.TP
.B devtools_report
The primary diagnostic tool.
Returns a complete report in a single call: JavaScript exceptions,
console errors and warnings, failed/broken network resources, and slow
requests.
Equivalent to reading the Console and Network tabs in DevTools simultaneously.
Accepts an optional \fIsince\fR ISO\~8601 timestamp to filter entries.
.TP
.B devtools_js_errors
Return buffered JavaScript exceptions only.
.TP
.B devtools_console
Return buffered console output.
Accepts an optional \fIlevel\fR filter (log, warn, error, info, debug).
.TP
.B devtools_network_failed
Return failed or slow network resources (4xx, 5xx, DNS errors, connection failures).
.TP
.B devtools_network_all
Return all captured network requests.
Accepts \fIresource_type\fR, \fImin_status\fR, \fIslow_ms\fR, \fIsince\fR,
and \fIlimit\fR filters.
Use \fIlimit\fR on busy pages to avoid overwhelming the context window.
.TP
.B devtools_clear
Clear all buffered console, JS error, and network entries.
Call this before navigating to a new page to get a clean baseline.
.TP
.B devtools_enable_bidi
Attach (or re\-attach) BiDi event listeners to the running session.
.TP
.B devtools_computed_css
Return computed (final applied) CSS properties for an element.
Useful for diagnosing hidden elements, wrong colours, or broken layouts.
.TP
.B devtools_element_info
Return detailed element info: outerHTML, bounding box, visibility,
viewport position, all HTML attributes, ARIA properties, and text content.
.TP
.B devtools_css_variables
Return CSS custom properties (\fB\-\-var\fR) defined on \fB:root\fR.
Useful for diagnosing missing design tokens or failed stylesheet loads.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GECKODRIVER_PATH
Absolute path to the \fBgeckodriver\fR binary.
Takes highest priority over PATH lookup and auto\-download.
.TP
.B GECKODRIVER_AUTO_INSTALL
Set to \fBfalse\fR to disable automatic geckodriver download via
\fBwebdriver\-manager\fR.
Default: \fBtrue\fR.
.TP
.B FIREFOX_BINARY
Path to a custom Firefox executable.
.TP
.B FIREFOX_PROFILE
Named Firefox profile to use (same as \fB\-P\fR).
.TP
.B FIREFOX_PROFILE_DIR
Profile directory path (same as \fB\-\-profile\fR).
Takes precedence over \fBFIREFOX_PROFILE\fR when both are set.
.SH GECKODRIVER RESOLUTION
The server searches for \fBgeckodriver\fR in this order (first match wins):
.IP 1. 4
\fBGECKODRIVER_PATH\fR environment variable
.IP 2. 4
System \fBPATH\fR \(em install with
\fBapt install gecko\-driver\fR from \fIhttp://repo.vitexsoftware.com\fR
.IP 3. 4
\fBwebdriver\-manager\fR auto\-download (if \fBGECKODRIVER_AUTO_INSTALL\fR \(!= \fBfalse\fR)
.SH USE CASES
The following scenarios illustrate the tool sequences an AI assistant uses
in practice.
.SS Debug a broken page
The assistant runs \fBdevtools_report\fR after navigating — the single call
returns JavaScript exceptions, console errors, and failed network resources
simultaneously, equivalent to reading the Console and Network tabs in
DevTools.
.PP
.RS
.EX
browser_open
browser_navigate  url=/dashboard
devtools_report
browser_screenshot
.EE
.RE
.SS Diagnose a CSS layout problem
.RS
.EX
browser_open
browser_navigate  url=/checkout
browser_screenshot
devtools_computed_css  selector=button#pay  properties=display,visibility,z-index
devtools_css_variables  prefix=--color
devtools_network_failed
.EE
.RE
.SS Automate a login flow
.RS
.EX
browser_open
browser_navigate  url=/login
browser_fill      selector=#username  value=admin
browser_fill      selector=#password  value=secret
browser_press_key key=enter
browser_wait      selector=#dashboard  condition=visible
browser_screenshot
devtools_report
.EE
.RE
.SS Inject a session cookie to bypass login
.RS
.EX
browser_open
browser_navigate  url=/
browser_set_cookie  name=session  value=<token>
browser_navigate  url=/admin
browser_screenshot
.EE
.RE
.SS Interact with a hover dropdown menu
.RS
.EX
browser_hover     selector=.nav-products
browser_wait      selector=.dropdown-menu  condition=visible
browser_find_elements  selector=.dropdown-menu a
browser_click     selector=.dropdown-menu a:nth-child(3)
.EE
.RE
.SS Scroll to lazy-loaded content
.RS
.EX
browser_open
browser_navigate  url=/feed
browser_scroll    by=true  y=1000
browser_wait      selector=.lazy-card  condition=present
browser_screenshot
.EE
.RE
.SS Handle a JS confirmation dialog
.RS
.EX
browser_click          selector=#delete-btn
browser_accept_dialog
browser_wait           selector=.success  condition=visible
.EE
.RE
.SS Audit page performance
.RS
.EX
browser_open
browser_navigate  url=/shop
devtools_network_all  slow_ms=500  limit=20
.EE
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the server with a named Firefox profile (session already logged in):
.PP
.RS
.EX
mcp\-server\-webdriver \-P work
.EE
.RE
.PP
Start with a profile directory:
.PP
.RS
.EX
mcp\-server\-webdriver \-\-profile /home/alice/.mozilla/firefox/abc123.dev
.EE
.RE
.PP
MCP client configuration (\fBclaude_desktop_config.json\fR):
.PP
.RS
.EX
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "webdriver": {
      "command": "mcp\-server\-webdriver",
      "args": ["\-P", "work"]
    }
  }
}
.EE
.RE
.PP
Install geckodriver from the VitexSoftware repository:
.PP
.RS
.EX
echo "deb http://repo.vitexsoftware.com trixie main" \\
  | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vitexsoftware.list
sudo apt update && sudo apt install gecko\-driver
.EE
.RE
